  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (bdc661f 2022-08-12T00:14:14.692552Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nanvil --fork-url\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nQuerying `eth_getProof` on Anvil with mainnet forking enabled returns `-32603: Required data unavailable` which is probably thrown here: https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/e71033db01a164fff45ff1a442ee7343886e64a4/anvil/src/eth/backend/mem/mod.rs#L1422. Querying directly via Alchemy works though.\r\n\r\nHere's a proof of concept: https://github.com/jo-es/anvil-poc",
